    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-09-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="572"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d572">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Melcoun Guedjian claims American citizenship; naturalized December, 1894;
                    passport State Department January, 1895. Landed secretly in Turkey, unarmed, as
                    the agent of Huntchaguist Revolutionary Society of London; was furnished with
                    £800 by the revolutionists, which he said was for the poor. Was arrested and
                    sentenced to long imprisonment at Aleppo, without notice to our consular agent.
                    I have protested against enforcement of sentence until I could examine. Does the
                    fact of his return to Turkey as the agent of a society organized against the
                    Government of Turkey forfeit American protection?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
